# Monorepo Workspace Rules

- Keep `apps/*` deployable and `packages/*` reusable.
- Place cross-app code in `packages/shared`, not by copying between apps.
- Use workspace-aware scripts from repo root for CI and production parity.
- Avoid app-to-app imports; apps may depend only on shared packages.

## Dependency Hygiene

- Add dependencies to the package that uses them.
- Prefer explicit internal package names (for example `@b2b/shared`).
- Remove unused dependencies during modernization tasks.

## Change Discipline

- When changing shared code, validate both app variants.
- Document any breaking API changes in shared package README or changelog notes.
